<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="../../images/kfilogos.gif"><BR>
<H1><CENTER>Keystone Financial Inc.</CENTER></H1>
<H2><CENTER>Third Quarter Report 1997</CENTER></H2>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<br>
<HR="#0000ff">

<H4>
We are pleased with our third quarter financial performance. As we continue
to face numerous competitive market challenges, we are confident that our
strategies to build market position by providing our customers with solutions
for their financial needs will enable us to maintain the growth momentum
of the past several years.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
Net income in the third quarter was $24.6 million, or $0.48 per share,
compared with $22.3 million or $0.43 per share in the same 1996 period.
Excluding the impact of the special charges and portfolio restructuring
losses taken during the second quarter of 1997, net income for the nine
months was $70.9 million or $1.37 per share, versus $66.7 million or $1.28
per share in 1996. We remain focused on two vital measures of performance
and are constantly at work to improve our returns on both equity and assets.
ROE for the quarter reached 14.64% while ROA was 1.43%. The competitive
marketplace is challenging us to achieve our goal of being in the top quartile
in these measures among banks in our peer group.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
Maintaining net interest income strength is critical to the success of
our organization and as a way of building this capability, we continue
to roll out new financial products at the same time we are strengthening
relationships on a customer-by-customer basis. Our newest product is KeyBuy,
a package of services that includes advising customers on new vehicle purchases,
financing the vehicle, and providing tips on how to get the best price
for their old car. Well suited to our emphasis on relationship banking,
KeyBuy helps customers do the research necessary to decide what buy is
best for them. Maximizing convenience, customers can access this program
through our Internet site.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
KeyBuy replaces the indirect automobile lending program, which we exited
this quarter, enabling us to serve customers directly and to create opportunities
to extend relationships through additional financial services. We believe
KeyBuy is a better way for us to serve the important automotive market.
Auto dealers remain important customers to us and we will continue to provide
financing for their inventories and offer additional services to them.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
Increases in fee income are being fueled by growing market recognition
of our programs and continuing investment in fee-based financial services.
During the third quarter, we acquired MMC&amp;P, a retirement benefit services
firm in Pittsburgh. This acquisition will increase our capabilities in
defined contribution recordkeeping and specialized retirement plan management,
enabling customers in Keystone's markets to attain outstanding service
levels for all of their employee benefit programs. The firm's president,
John Parks, assumes responsibility for Keystone's employee benefit trust
operations as we continue to grow our many resources in meeting the complete
financial needs of our customers.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
Indeed, investment market confidence in our asset management group is shown
in our steady rise of assets under management. Bill Martindale, chief investment
officer of our Martindale Andres investment management subsidiary, was
recently recognized in Money Magazine as one of the top portfolio managers
in the country. Martindale Andres &amp; Co. manages the KeyPremier family
of mutual funds, which was introduced earlier this year and has been accepted
well in the market. At present, the KeyPremier family consists of seven
separate mutual funds with assets expected to reach one billion by year-end.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
In addition to sharing information with you on our earnings growth and
other progress within the company, I would also like to announce the promotion
of Mark L. Pulaski to Vice Chairman and Chief Operating Officer. He was
also appointed as a member of the board of directors. In his new posts,
Mark will be responsible for all customer sales and support and related
administrative segments of the company. Mark previously served as Sr. Executive
Vice President, Chief Administrative Officer, and Chief Financial Officer.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
Concurrently, George H. Groves, Sr. Executive Vice President and Chief
Banking Officer, has resigned to pursue other business interests. George
has made many valuable contributions to the company over the past 12 years,
and we wish him well in his future endeavors.</H4>

<H4>
 <BR>
While we have experienced substantial growth over the last decade, we believe
our potential is still ahead of us. Our ability to build effective relationships
with customers and our investments in more products and services are distinguishing
Keystone as the financial institution of choice in our markets. We thank
you for your continued support as we continue to build shareholder value.</H4>

