<HR NOSHADE>
<H2>
FINANCIAL SUMMARY</H2>

<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 >
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSTART="1"><IMG SRC="retavgassets.gif" ></TD>

<TD VALIGN=TOP COLSTART="2">
<H4>
Keystone recorded earnings growth as third quarter net income reached $24,600,000
or $0.48 per share, compared to $22,287,000 or $0.43 per share for the
same period last year. Earnings per share growth was 11.6% from the third
quarter of 1996 to the same period in 1997.
<BR>
<br>
Net income for the nine-month period declined to $62,353,000 or $1.21 per
share, from $66,717,000 or $1.28 per share in 1996. Excluding the impact
of the special charges and portfolio restructuring losses taken during
the second quarter of 1997, net income for the nine months was $1.37, up
from $1.28 for the same period in 1996, resulting in a return on average
assets of 1.44% and a return on average equity of 14.44%.
<BR>
<br>
Operating performance for Keystone continued to reflect underlying strength
and was influenced by both stable net interest margin and growth in noninterest
revenues, including security gains. Net interest income grew over 10% since
the third quarter of 1996, including loan growth of over 11% and a net
interest margin of 4.62%. Noninterest revenues grew over 16%, reflecting
increases in nearly all revenue categories. </H4>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 >
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSTART="1"><IMG SRC="retavgequity.gif" ></TD>

<TD VALIGN=TOP COLSTART="2">
<H4>
During the third quarter, Keystone was able to complete the conversions
of Financial Trust Corporation and First Financial Corporation of Western
Maryland to Keystone's various systems and applications. This effort will
position Keystone's new partners and their customers to take full advantage
of the complete array of financial products and services available through
Keystone.
<BR>
<br>
The additional time and effort to convert and consolidate operating systems
of merger partners resulted in increased salary expenses during the period.
However, this effort is expected to improve the operating efficiency in
the fourth quarter and beyond. Despite the effect of the expenses associated
with the conversions and consolidations, Keystone's ratio of noninterest
expenses to revenues remained constant at 58.51%, and further improvement
is expected.
<BR><br>
Asset quality ratios continue to reflect underlying strength, despite national
trends of higher consumer delinquency levels. Key measures included ratios
of nonperforming assets to loans of 0.59% and total risk elements to loans
of 1.10%, both of which are stable compared to historical results.</H4>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<HR NOSHADE>
<H2>
CORPORATE PROFILE</H2>

<H4>
Keystone Financial, Inc. is the fourth largest bank holding company headquartered
in Pennsylvania. Seven member banks provide a wide range of financial products
and services through nearly 200 community offices in central and southeastern
Pennsylvania, Maryland, and West Virginia. In addition to its community
banking network, Keystone operates several other companies including mortgage,
trust and asset management, retirement benefit services and leasing.</H4>

