<H2>
Information On Dividends</H2>

<H3>
Dividend Reinvestment Plan:</H3>

<H4>
Shareholders of Keystone Financial may acquire additional shares of common
stock with their dividends through a Dividend Reinvestment Plan. Voluntary
cash payments may also be made under this plan on a quarterly basis.</H4>

<H3>
Direct Deposit:</H3>

<H4>
Shareholders may have their cash dividends deposited directly into the
account of their choice at any banking institution. The cash amount will
be deposited on the date the dividend is payable, and a confirmation of
payment from the transfer agent will be sent.<BR>
<br>
Additional information and enrollment materials for both of these options
can be obtained by writing to the Transfer Agent:</H4>

<CENTER>American Stock Transfer &amp; Trust Co.</CENTER>

<CENTER>Attn: Shareholder Services</CENTER>

<CENTER>40 Wall Street</CENTER>

<CENTER>New York, NY 10005</CENTER>

<H3>
<I>Stock Listing</I></H3>

<H4>
The common stock of Keystone Financial, Inc. is traded in the over-the-counter
market under the symbol KSTN and is listed in the National Market System
of NASDAQ.</H4>

